shared_text:
CCS District 135
September 4 at 11:59 AM ·

Centralia City School District 135 will remain on our normal schedule and continue with in person learning as usual. We are coordinating with the local health departments on a daily basis to ensure that in person learning can continue safely, and have not been advised to place our district under any further restrictions at this time. The temporary pause in student attendance at Centralia High School will not affect any students attending Centralia City Schools unless they are notified by the Health Department on an individual basis. The Marion County Health Department has informed us that the positive cases that have been identified at the high school do not have a direct connection to our students or staff members. We will continue to follow guidance from IDPH, the CDC, and our local health departments and we thank you for your continued support.

September 3 at 7:20 AM ·

I want to give a huge shoutout to Centralia Illinois Police Department and Officer Denton

This child was scared of cops a few weeks ago. Now every morning she demands her window is down so she can say good morning and have a good day to Officer Denton.

She insisted that Officer Denton and his friends needed cupcakes.

Thank you Officer Denton for everything you do.

Think you have a great theme for the Halloween parade? See the information below!

The theme contest is open to all grade school kids in the Centralia City school system. They can submit their theme idea along with their NAME, AGE, GRADE, and SCHOOL. They can email it to:

contest@centraliahalloweenparade.com

OR mail to: Halloween Parade, PO Box 410, Centralia, IL 62801

Entries must be emailed or postmarked by midnight, May 23rd, 2020

The winner will ride in the parade as a VIP and win a pizza party for his or her class. The party will be held when school resumes in the fall.

post_text:
To say this was no ordinary year is an understatement! It was not always easy, but together, we made it through this crazy quarter. Please see the image below for a few important points.

We know there is also a lot of a speculation floating around about how next year will look. We encourage everyone to take a deep breath and be patient (easier said than done!). One thing we have learned is that information changes rapidly. Rest assured that we will work hard to plan for WHATEVER situations we may encounter in the fall using what we have learned throughout all of this.

But for now, HAPPY LAST DAY OF SCHOOL! 🥳🎉🎈

Important dates!

Students, this is the last instructional week! Make sure to get your work turned in, either online or packets (packets can always be dropped off in the orange bins).

Parents, the next (and final) drop off/item pick up is Friday, May 22. ALL items (library books, any text books, spring pictures or money, etc.) are due. This is the last opportunity to send someone to pick up items from lockers.

Report card info. will be posted later this week.

Graduate picture sign up times are available via the link that was shared on the CJHS Facebook page on Friday (these are not mandatory). If your child comes for pictures, he/she will be given their diploma and cover at that time IF they have met all of their academic obligations and all items have been turned in (or fees paid). If they do not come for pictures OR if they have not met their academic obligations, have fines, etc., then arrangements will be made to get diplomas and covers to those students.

Hang in there, everyone, we are almost there! 💜

8th grade parents, below is the link to sign up if you wish to have your child's picture taken in the gym with his/her diploma.
Information on procedures will be sent out to those who sign up.

Once we are finished, the pictures will be sent to Walgreens as they have been in years past, and parents will be given the information on how to purchase images if they wish to do so. These pictures are not required; they are being offered if you would like a picture of your child in his/her gown in the CJHS gym. In order to maintain the health and safety of all involved, appropriate social distancing will be maintained and strict limits on the number of people in the building will be in place. Only students will be permitted inside the building in order to help meet this requirement. Thank you for your understanding.

post_text:
Beginning today, Illinois families with school-age children can apply for extra money for food through the Pandemic EBT (P-EBT). Families currently receiving SNAP do not need to apply for P-EBT benefits, because these additional P-EBT benefits will be automatically loaded into Illinois LINK EBT accounts. Families who do not currently receive SNAP benefits but have children who receive free or reduced-priced meals will need to apply directly with the Illinois Department of Human Services (IDHS).

https://abe.illinois.gov/abe/access/

post_text: We would like to congratulate Ms. Piercy, CJHS 7th-grade language arts teacher, on receiving an award for academic achievement from McKendree University. Ms. Piercy was recognized for "excellence in the study of middle school education...based on four major components of McKendree University's mission: responsible citizenship, engagement, academic excellence, and lifelong learning." Ms. Piercy began student teaching with Mrs. Burdin in the fall of this year, and she graduated in December. When CJHS unexpectedly had an opening in 7th-grade language arts beginning with the second semester, we were very fortunate that Ms. Piercy wanted to permanently become part of our CJHS family! Congratulations, Ms. Piercy!

CCS District 135
April 17 at 2:39 PM ·

IMPORTANT ANNOUNCEMENT FROM THE SUPERINTENDENT:

Centralia City Schools Family,

The Governor’s announcement today that school will be closed for the remainder of the year is sobering. However, the Board of Education, principals, teachers, and support staff are dedicated to continuing meaningful learning opportunities, food service, and student and family support until the end of the school year. Over the next few days, the administrative team will continue the process of reviewing and analyzing our current Remote Learning Plan. We will adapt as needed and work hard to make sure you are up to date on current information as we have it. Remember to look to www.ccs135.com for all information and updates on our school closure page. I am extremely proud of the way everyone has handled this difficult situation. Your support and encouragement has helped to keep us motivated. Thank you and stay safe.

Mr. Clark
Superintendent
Centralia City Schools District 135

post_text:
Central Middle School/Centralia Jr. High School Parents,

Over the weekend, teachers have been hard at work making preparations for how to best meet the needs of our students through the upcoming days. Tomorrow, your children will be given instruction on how to access Google classroom (if they do not use it already), and teachers will be posting activities for them for the week. This is also a way for students and parents to connect with teachers if needed. For those who may not have access to technology, teachers will send home packets with similar activities to those being posted. We want all of our students to have access to continued learning over the days of this closure.

We strongly encourage everyone to make sure their child completes daily work so that he/she can continue to grow academically. More information will be sent home with students tomorrow.

Thank you,
Mrs. Becker
Principal

shared_text:
CCS District 135
March 14 at 7:57 PM ·

March 14, 2020, School Closure Update:

After meeting and planning today, our district administrative team has come up with an educational plan, as well as, a breakfast/lunch distribution plan for the upcoming school closure. An informational packet will be going home with all students on Monday.

Please continue to check our social media pages for updates and information. We will be using these pages to relay information as soon as it is released to us. Please note, plans are subject to change as we adjust to new mandates passed down to us from the state. Thank you for your patience and understanding as we continue to try to serve our students’ educational needs as best we can during this time.

*Jordan Elementary, Schiller Elementary, Central Middle, and Centralia Jr. High Schools will be closed from March 17 - March 30, 2020.*

shared_text:
CCS District 135
March 13 at 10:15 AM ·

As we continue to monitor the COVID-19 issue, we wanted to update you on what Centralia City Schools Dist. 135 is doing proactively to stop the spread of any germs:

- We are staying in contact with the local Health Department and state officials, as well as, closely monitoring the CDC website to make sure we have all the most up to date information and guidelines.

- Our custodians and kitchen staff are cleaning beyond their normal guidelines with CDC approved disinfecting cleaners.

- Our buses are also being cleaned daily with CDC approved disinfecting cleaners.

The school board, administration, faculty, and staff of Centralia City Schools Dist. 135 are taking the COVID-19 virus seriously. We will continue to follow all guidelines to help stop the spread of any germs. The best course of action is to keep washing your hands, disinfecting frequently touched objects/surfaces, covering your cough or sneeze, and avoid touching your eyes, nose, and mouth. And remember - stay home if you are sick!

*If your child is sick, please call in to the school and the absence will be excused.*
